{"questionId":"7711","questionHtml":"<p>Determine the magnification of the microscope.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><em><strong>ALTERNATIVE 1:</strong></em></p>\n<p>eyepiece: <em>m</em> =&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{ - v}}{u} = \\frac{{240}}{{28}}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mo>−</mo>\n      <mi>v</mi>\n    </mrow>\n    <mi>u</mi>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>240</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>28</mn>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span> = 5&nbsp;✔</p>\n<p><em><strong>AND</strong></em></p>\n<p>objective&nbsp;<em>m</em>&nbsp;=&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{ - v}}{u} = \\frac{{ - 120}}{{24}}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mo>−</mo>\n      <mi>v</mi>\n    </mrow>\n    <mi>u</mi>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mo>−</mo>\n      <mn>120</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>24</mn>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span> =&nbsp;−5&nbsp;✔</p>\n<p>Total&nbsp;<em>m</em>&nbsp;=&nbsp;−5&nbsp;× 5 =&nbsp;−25&nbsp;✔</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>ALTERNATIVE 2:</strong></em></p>\n<p><em>m</em>&nbsp;=&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\left( {\\frac{{240}}{{60}} + 1} \\right) \\times \\left( { - \\frac{{120}}{{24}}} \\right)\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mfrac>\n        <mrow>\n          <mn>240</mn>\n        </mrow>\n        <mrow>\n          <mn>60</mn>\n        </mrow>\n      </mfrac>\n      <mo>+</mo>\n      <mn>1</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>×</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mo>−</mo>\n      <mfrac>\n        <mrow>\n          <mn>120</mn>\n        </mrow>\n        <mrow>\n          <mn>24</mn>\n        </mrow>\n      </mfrac>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>&nbsp;✔</p>\n<p><em>m</em>&nbsp;=&nbsp;−25&nbsp;✔</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em>Accept positive or negative values throughout.</em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"7711","referenceCode":"18N.3.SL.TZ0.9b.ii","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"Determine the magnification of the microscope.","paper":"3","level":"SL","questionNumber":"b.ii","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Option C: Imaging","Option C: Imaging","Option C: Imaging (Core topics)","C.2 – Imaging instrumentation","Option C: Imaging","Option C: Imaging (Core topics)"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}